    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>French ball game played between two players or teams, who take turns throwing or rolling a ball or boule, usually made of steel, as close as possible to the target ball, called the jack, or cochonnet. If necessary, the player will use his ball to knock the opponent's ball away. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
